T1  - A Model of Exchange Rate Determination under Currency Substitution and Rational Expectations
AU  - Calvo, Guillermo A.
AU  - Rodriguez, Carlos Alfredo
Y1  - 1977/06/01
PY  - 1977
DA  - 1977/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.1086/260586
DO  - 10.1086/260586
T2  - Journal of Political Economy
JF  - Journal of Political Economy
SP  - 617
EP  - 625
VL  - 85
IS  - 3
PB  - The University of Chicago Press
N2  - This paper analyzes a two-sector model of exchange rate determination for a mall open economy with flexible prices. Residents are assumed to hold both domestic and foreign currency and to have rational expectations. The model satisfies the homogeneity postulate but it is shown that an increase in the rate of expansions of money supply leads to an instantaneous deterioration of the real exchange rate. In the long run, however, the latter moves back to its previous level.
AB  - This paper analyzes a two-sector model of exchange rate determination for a mall open economy with flexible prices. Residents are assumed to hold both domestic and foreign currency and to have rational expectations. The model satisfies the homogeneity postulate but it is shown that an increase in the rate of expansions of money supply leads to an instantaneous deterioration of the real exchange rate. In the long run, however, the latter moves back to its previous level.
SN  - 0022-3808
M3  - doi: 10.1086/260586
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1086/260586
Y2  - 2024/03/22
